<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, adults of this species are active throughout the spring and are generally found in proximity to artificial lights at night. Their range in total length is 9-11 mm, and 1.5-3 in maximum width. In nearby Hong Kong, larvae of this species bore into 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rutaceae" genus="Citrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Citrus" order="Rutales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Citrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. plants (
<bibRefCitation author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Other larval host plants include 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Diospyros kaki" order="Ebenales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="kaki">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Diospyros kaki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Osmeridae" genus="Mallotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mallotus japonicas" order="Osmeriformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="japonicas">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Mallotus japonicas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus acuta" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="acuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Quercus acuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5656/KSAE.2013.11.1.061" author="Lim, J" journalOrPublisher="Korean Journal of Applied Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="111 - 133" refId="B87" refString="Lim, J, Jung, S-Y, Lim, J-S, Jang, J, Kim, K-M, Lee, Y-M, Lee, B-W, 2014. A Review of Host Plants of Cerambycidae (Coleoptera: Chrysomeloidea) with new Host Records for Fourteen Cerambycids, Including the Asian Longhorn Beetle (Anoplophora glabripennis Motschulsky), in Korea. Korean Journal of Applied Entomology 53 (2): 111 - 133, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5656/KSAE.2013.11.1.061" title="A Review of Host Plants of Cerambycidae (Coleoptera: Chrysomeloidea) with new Host Records for Fourteen Cerambycids, Including the Asian Longhorn Beetle (Anoplophora glabripennis Motschulsky), in Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.5656/KSAE.2013.11.1.061" volume="53" year="2014">Lim et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
), and in Japan even cultivated 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Prunus salicina" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="salicina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Prunus salicina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kusigemati, K" journalOrPublisher="Memoires of the Faculty of Agriculture, Kagoshima University" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="199 - 202" refId="B78" refString="Kusigemati, K, 1985. A new Ichneumonid-Parasite of the Cerambycid Beetle Ceresium longicorne Pic in Japan (Hymenoptera). Memoires of the Faculty of Agriculture, Kagoshima University 21: 199 - 202" title="A new Ichneumonid-Parasite of the Cerambycid Beetle Ceresium longicorne Pic in Japan (Hymenoptera)." volume="21" year="1985">Kusigemati 1985</bibRefCitation>
